response: "{ \"title\": \"[Easy] Factorial Calculator\", \"description\": \"Write a function `factorial` that calculates the factorial of a given number.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef factorial(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A non-negative integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the factorial of the input number.\", \"code\": \"def factorial(n: int) -> int:\\n    if n == 0 or n == 1:\\n        return 1\\n    else:\\n        fact = 1\\n        for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n            fact *= i\\n        return fact\", \"tests\": [\"assert factorial(5) == 120\", \"assert factorial(0) == 1\", \"assert factorial(1) == 1\", \"assert factorial(6) == 720\"] }"
